I"H<p>I got invited to participate in a survey on LinkedIn. It was about ThymeLeaf. I used ThymeLeaft for a bit during my first job. So, I decided to do it. The survey was on G2 and I got a $10 virtual card as a reward for participating.</p>

<p>I was thinking of things where I could use this virtual card. It’s an international card, so I could use it in most of the sites I wanted to. The very first thing I did was to sign up for AWS 1 year free tier account. I also tried to sign up for GCP, but unfortunately they don’t support Virtual Cards.</p>

<p>Buying a custom domain seemed to be the perfect thing for me. So, I headed on to GoDaddy and looked what’s available. After some digging, I settled for jahir.me. It was cheap, short and easy to remember. I got it for like 3$ for 1 year.</p>

<p>This was the first time I was managing a domain and these things seemed pretty complex. I still have to Google everytime I need to change a CNAME record. Besides that I found GoDaddy’s domain management interface poorly designed. So, I moved my domain management to Cloudfare. I find their interface quite intuitive and easy to use. I also got a https site for free. Sweet deal!</p>

<p>For future domains, I’ll probably buy it directly from Cloudflare or use Namecheap. Those seem to be the better options with better tools than GoDaddy.</p>
